    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_gt.00017_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">New York</name>
                    <date when="1882-05-28" rend="right">May 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>,
                        1882</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I thought I would write a few lines to let you know how I am a getting along<!--<ptr target="n0883"/>--> &#38;
                how I like the Steam Boat. I like it middling well but cant tell much about it yet. We expect to take a
                trip to New Berg on Tuesday next. Perhaps I can tell you more about it after we
                start. </p>
            <p>(I have had a <choice>
                    <orig>verry</orig>
                    <reg>very</reg>
                </choice> good time Uncle <choice>
                    <orig>Vandoran</orig>
                    <reg>Van Doran</reg>
                </choice> and I <choice>
                    <orig>is</orig>
                    <reg>are</reg>
                </choice> getting ready to go out to Central Park this after noon
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_gt.00018_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                     for tomorrow we have got to go to work and <choice>
                    <orig>wont</orig>
                    <reg>won't</reg>
                </choice> be apt to
                get <choice>
                    <orig>anether</orig>
                    <reg>another</reg>
                </choice> chance to go soon. I have received <choice>
                    <orig>to</orig>
                    <reg>two</reg>
                </choice> letters from home. <choice>
                    <orig>they</orig>
                    <reg>They</reg>
                </choice> say they are all well &#38; Ruth<!--<ptr target="nyp.00408_n4"/>--> says she will have a situation for me when <choice>
                    <orig>i</orig>
                    <reg>I</reg>
                </choice> get home to scrub and wash dishes when she <choice>
                        <sic>rote</sic>
                        <corr>wrote</corr>
                    </choice> to me she wanted to know if I had to scrub.</p>
            <p>I have <choice>
                    <orig>rode</orig>
                    <reg>ridden</reg>
                </choice> all around New York on the elevated Rail Way &#38; have seen grand times.
                We <choice>
                    <orig>dont</orig>
                    <reg>don't</reg>
                </choice> know <choice>
                    <orig>weather</orig>
                    <reg>whether</reg>
                </choice> the Boat will run up to long Branch or not
                they will try at new burg 
                <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_gt.00019_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
                <choice><orig>firs</orig><reg>first</reg></choice> &amp; if it pay
                they will continue on
                all Summer. You must come on to New York this summer and take a trip with us, that is
                if I stay here. You must excuse <choice><sic>m</sic><corr>my</corr></choice> writing &#38; spelling for I am in a hurry to get off to the
                park.</p>
            <p>Write Soon and let me know how you are</p>
            <p>I will try &#38; write a little more <choice><orig>abou</orig><reg>about</reg></choice> thing next time</p>
            <p>I write &#38; send my
                love to you, hopeing to <choice><sic>herr</sic><corr>hear</corr></choice> from you Soon,</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Van</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript> 
            <p><address><addrLine>Directions</addrLine>
<addrLine>439 East 23<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi> st</addrLine>
            <addrLine>Steamer (<choice><orig>Plymoth</orig><reg>Plymouth</reg></choice>) Rock</addrLine>
            <addrLine>New York</addrLine></address></p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
                <salute>From your friend.</salute>
                <signed rend="right">Van</signed>
            </closer>
